-- Egypt's Finance Ministry May Invest in Refinery, Masry al Youm Reports
-- B y   O l a   G a l a l
-- 2010-12-14T06:11:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-14/egypt-s-finance-ministry-may-invest-in-refinery-masry-says.html
Egypt’s Finance Ministry is studying
investing in Egyptian Refining Co.’s $3.7 billion refinery,  Al
Masry Al Youm  reported, citing Amr El-Garhy, vice chairman of
the state-run National Investment Bank.  The ministry, represented by the bank and the country’s
Health Insurance Authority, will in the next two weeks decide on
the possible size of the stake, the newspaper cited El-Garhy as
saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ola Galal in Cairo at 
 ogalal@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
 sev@bloomberg.net . 